[% META title = 'Theme System Documentation' %]
[% PageVersion = 'static/css/README_THEME_SYSTEM.tt,v 0.01 2025/01/19 shanta Exp shanta ' %]
[% debug %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
    [% "Debugging HostName: " _ HostName %]
    [%# INCLUDE 'debug.tt' %]
[% END %]

<div class="documentation-content theme-system-docs">
    <h1>Theme System Documentation</h1>

    <section class="overview">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>The theme system has been refactored to use CSS variables and a centralized approach. This allows for easier customization and maintenance of themes.</p>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <strong>Latest Updates</strong>: See <a href="/Documentation/changelog/2025-01-19-css-theme-system-enhancements.tt">CSS Theme System Enhancements - January 2025</a> for recent improvements including interactive CSS editor and enhanced theme management.
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="file-structure">
        <h2>Files Structure</h2>
        <ul class="file-list">
            <li><code>/static/css/base.css</code> - Contains base styles and CSS variables</li>
            <li><code>/static/css/menu-theme.css</code> - Contains menu styles using theme variables</li>
            <li><code>/static/css/theme-overrides.css</code> - Contains theme-specific overrides</li>
            <li><code>/static/css/themes/</code> - Directory containing theme-specific CSS files:
                <ul class="theme-files">
                    <li><code>default.css</code></li>
                    <li><code>csc.css</code></li>
                    <li><code>apis.css</code></li>
                    <li><code>usbm.css</code></li>
                    <li>etc.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="how-it-works">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>The <code>Header.tt</code> file includes:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>base.css</code> - Base styles with variables</li>
                    <li>Theme-specific CSS file (e.g., <code>themes/csc.css</code>)</li>
                    <li><code>menu-theme.css</code> - Menu styles using theme variables</li>
                    <li><code>theme-overrides.css</code> - Additional theme overrides</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Each theme CSS file defines CSS variables and theme-specific styles.</li>
            <li>The body element gets a theme-specific class (e.g., <code>theme-csc</code>) to allow for theme-specific styling.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="adding-new-theme">
        <h2>Adding a New Theme</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Create a new CSS file in <code>/static/css/themes/</code> (e.g., <code>mytheme.css</code>)</li>
            <li>Define CSS variables and theme-specific styles</li>
            <li>Add the theme to the list of valid themes in <code>ThemeManager.pm</code></li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="migration">
        <h2>Migrating from Old CSS System</h2>
        <p>The old CSS system used separate CSS files for each site:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>CSCCSSView.css</code></li>
            <li><code>menu.css</code></li>
            <li>etc.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>These have been replaced with the theme system. If you need to add styles from the old system:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Extract the relevant styles</li>
            <li>Convert them to use CSS variables where appropriate</li>
            <li>Add them to the appropriate theme CSS file</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="background-images">
        <h2>Background Images</h2>
        <p>To add a background image to a theme:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Place the image in <code>/static/images/[THEME_NAME]/</code></li>
            <li>In the theme CSS file, add:</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="code-example">
            <pre><code>body {
    background-image: url('../../images/[THEME_NAME]/background.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-attachment: fixed;
}</code></pre>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="menu-styling">
        <h2>Menu Styling</h2>
        <p>Menu styles are now in <code>menu-theme.css</code> and use theme variables. To customize menu styles for a specific theme, add overrides in the theme CSS file or in <code>theme-overrides.css</code>.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="troubleshooting">
        <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
        <p>If styles are not applying correctly:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Check browser developer tools to see which CSS files are being loaded</li>
            <li>Verify that the theme class is being added to the body element</li>
            <li>Check for CSS specificity issues (use <code>!important</code> sparingly if needed)</li>
            <li>Clear browser cache</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
</div>